figure_1: Cumulative incidence rates of breast cancer and 95% confidence intervals in women with and without benign breast disease within year at index mammogram strata; (A) 1996–2000, (B) 2001–2005, (C) 2006–2010, (D) 2011–2015. The solid line represents women without benign breast disease; the hyphen line represents women with a benign breast disease diagnosis.
figure_2: Cumulative incidence rates of breast cancer and 95% confidence intervals in women with and without benign breast disease within age at index mammogram strata; (A) 50–54, (B) 55–59, (C) 60–64, (D) 65–69. The solid line represents women without benign breast disease; the hyphen line represents women with a benign breast disease diagnosis.
figure_3: Crude and adjusted rate ratios of incidence breast cancer in women with benign breast disease at screening during January 1996 to December 2015, according to year at index mammogram, age at index mammogram, and time since index mammogram. Adjusted rate ratios by year, age, and time since index mammogram simultaneously.
